track_notes: I believe this is the shortest route from a parking area to the summit. Snake Den tr, a bit of Maddron Bald tr, then the AT. Begin bushwack at N35 42.458’ W83 15.530’ and have the summit marked.

This is for a double activation of Old Black and Mount Guyot.   This involves off trail bush whacks to summit each peak.   The Mount Guyot bushwhack is based on the cairn point submitted by N0MAP.   The Old Black bush whack point is based on the suggestion by Ed Wendell from Peakbagger.com.   The track starts from the parking area in Cosby Campground.  The trail starts out on Snake Den Trail which starts out as a gravel road.  It then joins the AT at mile 5.56
Maybe a 20 min bushwhack from the AT through downfall spruce/fir forest.  Pay attention to minimal trail path from previous peakbaggers and you will be fine.  Dean ~ K2JB
